chapterNotes:
In heading 2523, "sagol" means cement obtained by heating limestone and burnt coal in a kiln;
and "ashmoh" means cement obtained by fine grinding of paddy husk, ash and hydrated lime
with an additive.

policyConditions.description:
Other clays (not including expanded clays of heading 68.06),
andalusite, kyanite and sillimanite, whether or not calcined; mullite;
chamotte or dinas earths.
